<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-10-31T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-10-31T01:00:00-05:00" n="622" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d622">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 Moscow/92: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">American
                                    Delegation</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-10-31T02:00:00-04:00">October
                                    31, 1943—2 a.m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>1143. Amdel 63. For McDermott. Reference Department’s 1138<note n="52" xml:id="d622fn52">October 30, 8 p.m., <ref target="#pg_684">p.
                                    684</ref>.</note> and your 1788<note n="53" xml:id="d622fn53">Telegram No. Delam 43, October 30, 9 a.m., <ref target="#pg_671">p.
                                    671</ref>.</note> (Amdel 61 and Delam 43). In order to
                            synchronize the plans outlined in our messages under reference we
                            propose to give correspondents in Washington text of documents at 2 p.m.
                            for publication at 5 p.m., Eastern War Time, November 1st. As indicated
                            in our 1138, no assurance possible here that German stories will not be
                            rebroadcast or published in this country in advance of agreed release
                            time.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>